The White House Press Secretary released a statement on the anniversary of the San Bernardino attack, acknowledging the horror and impact it had on the people of San Bernardino and the entire country. The statement reflects on the victims who were taken from us that day, highlighting their diverse backgrounds and selflessness. It also mentions the ongoing efforts to confront the violent ideology behind the attack and terrorist groups like ISIL. The statement ends by recognizing the progress made in the campaign against terrorism and reiterating the President's belief in succeeding because "we are on the right side of history."